# Data Science with Python 

#### The Data Science units are designed to be modular, meaning you can choose to teach one or both lessons depending on the needs of your course and your students.  

#### Unit 2 focuses on how to use **Pandas** and **Matplotlab** libraries in Python. 

<br>

<img src="https://images.code.org/1fbd805fdb9a29707582dcb5fb934d4a-image-1731943408107.png" alt="A red push pin. This icon is used to signal a callback to synchronous work in the workshop." width="40px" style="border-radius:10px; float:left; margin: 5px 10px 5px 0px;">

#### **Pandas** is a Python library for working with structured data, like tables or spreadsheets. It helps you clean, organize, analyze, and even visualize data easily, making it a go-to tool for data science and analysis.

<br>

<img src="https://images.code.org/11d076b1ccbee63578b9ac994b068707-image-1731943597800.png" alt="A red push pin. This icon is used to signal a callback to synchronous work in the workshop." width="50px" style="border-radius:10px; float:left; margin: 5px 3px 5px 0px;">

#### **Matplotlib** is a Python library for creating visualizations like charts and graphs. It makes it easy to turn data into clear, customizable visuals for analysis and presentations.

